They can also get queries answered. The answers to these is in the affirmative.” Usually people fear that HIV/AIDS can spread through hugging or holding hands, eating together, sharing clothes or house with an infected person, which is not true. HIV virus also does not stay alive more than a few minutes. The social protection portal section is a searchable database on social welfare schemes relevant to most at risk populations. Facilities related to HIV include information of counselling and testing services – ICTCs, ART (anti-retro viral) centres, blood banks, Suraksha clinics (for treatment of sexually transmitted infections), and for treatment of opoid injecting drug users.

